{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a square baking tin (approx. 20 cm) with greaseproof paper.","Place a jug on mixing bowl lid then weigh in 75 g almond milk. Remove jug and set aside.","Place nut spread and syrup in mixing bowl then melt <b>4 min\/100°C\/speed 2<b>.","Add rolled oats, oat bran, puffed rice, cocoa powder, protein powder and peppermint extract then stir <b>20 sec\/\/speed 3<b>. Remove bowl and leave to cool for 10 minutes.","Place mixing bowl back into position then add chocolate chips and stir <b>15 sec\/\/speed 2<b>.","Without measuring cup, mix <b>without time\/\/speed 2<b>, while adding reserved almond milk slowly through hole in mixing bowl lid until mixture loosens (all 75 g may not be needed). Transfer to prepared tin and press down with the back of a spoon. Cover and place in fridge for at least 4 hours or overnight.","Once chilled, remove from tin and cut into 12 bars. Wrap in greaseproof paper and serve or keep refrigerated for up to 5 days."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["75 g almond milk, or other non-dairy milk","125 g hazelnut cocoa spread","100 g agave syrup","135 g rolled oats","25 g oat bran","50 g puffed rice","25 g cocoa powder, unsweetened","20 g protein powder","8 - 10 drops peppermint extract, to taste","90 g dark chocolate chips"]}],"id":"r147877","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-S8W2cE0dgDY\/XZaq5NnnhqI\/AAAAAAAAhiU\/CJYJyiLQtFwlPcDJwRt6kvWTgeNOxsutgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_tE1D5ZPXkV4hUY4T.png","title":"Chewy Mint Choc Protein Bites","publishedAt":"2017-04-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"4.9 g","fat":"7.4 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"28.2 g","calories":"834 kJ \/ 199 kcal"},"usefulItems":"square baking tin (20 cm), greaseproof paper, jug, cling film, long sharp knife, refrigerator","basicInfo":["easy","15m","4h 25m","12 pieces"]}